│ sequence, so all newly created insertelements and shuffles are placed in a single block that dominates their    │
│ uses. I will search for IRBuilder insertion point handling near the vector construction and update it to set    │
│ the insertion point to the first insertion block (e.g., the start of Builder.GetInsertBlock()) before calling   │
